# ðŸ“± Expo EAS Build Guide (Android .aab)

# 1. Login to Expo (required before builds)
npx expo login

# 2. Configure EAS for the project (creates eas.json if missing)
eas build:configure

# 3. Clean project and regenerate native folders (use when icons/splash/config are changed)
npx expo prebuild --clean

# 4. Run locally on a connected Android device/emulator (debug build)
npx expo run:android

# 5. Create a development build (used for internal testing with Expo Go replacement)
eas build -p android --profile development

# 6. Create a preview build (for sharing with testers before production release)
eas build -p android --profile preview

# 7. Create a production build (.aab) for Google Play Store
eas build -p android --profile production

# 8. Check build status and get download links
eas build:list

# 9. Upload the generated .aab to Google Play Console:
#    â†’ Go to https://play.google.com/console/
#    â†’ Select your app â†’ Production â†’ Releases â†’ Create new release
#    â†’ Upload .aab, add release notes, review, and roll out
